In a press briefing on April 23, 2009, White House Press Secretary Robert Gibbs made several announcements. President Obama was scheduled to address the annual meeting of the National Academy of Sciences on Monday. The President also met with the new Ambassador to Iraq, Chris Hill, before his departure for Iraq. Later that day, the President was set to meet with bipartisan leadership in Congress to discuss priorities for the upcoming work session, including health care reform, energy independence, and the budget. Additionally, on Wednesday, April 29, the President would hold a news conference in the East Room of the White House. The briefing also touched on the possibility of an independent commission to look at the interrogations during the Bush era, the credit card industry, security in Iraq, oversight of government spending, and the release of interrogation memos.